transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Yeah, thanks for calling Viagra. How can I help you?

Speaker 2: Yeah, I had recently gotten an order, and I talked to somebody a little while ago.

Speaker 1: They sent me the wrong prescription, and he said he was going to rectify it and fix it.

Speaker 2: And then when I got confirmation of the new prescription,

Speaker 1: it seemed to be the same stuff that I got that I wasn't supposed to get.

Speaker 2: What's your first and last name?

Speaker 1: Yeah, my first name is Joe. My last name is Telmos. T-E-L-M-O-S.

Speaker 2: All right, Joe. Let me see what's going on here.

Speaker 1: You definitely shouldn't have gotten the same thing.

Speaker 2: But let me pull up your info and see what's happening.

Speaker 1: Yeah, I was supposed to get the Viagra ABG.

Speaker 2: Oh, and they sent me –

Speaker 1: Yeah, the new thing. That's why. The new order –

Speaker 2: Well, but they sent me like a –

Speaker 1: Thank you for using Blue Score, your treatment, your safety information.

Speaker 2: But then it says the thing they sent me on was the Filidophil again?

Speaker 1: Yeah. So that's the name, like the scientific name of the medicine, Filidophil.

Speaker 2: The Viagra ABG?

Speaker 1: Yeah, exactly. That's not important.

Speaker 2: Okay. No, no. I just wanted to make sure.

Speaker 1: Yeah. The manufacturer that it comes from, it'll be different.

Speaker 2: You'll see the markings on the pills will be different when you get them, Joe.

Speaker 1: And then the label will be different as well.

Speaker 2: No, and he told me all that.

Speaker 1: But then I got this, and I'm like, man, I just wanted to call and make sure

Speaker 2: they're not sending me the same stuff.

Speaker 1: No, he's doing it the right way.

Speaker 2: You're going to get the correct thing this time.

Speaker 1: Okay. The Viagra ABG 100?

Speaker 2: Exactly.

Speaker 1: Okay, perfect. Thank you so much. Sorry to bother you.

Speaker 2: Thank you. No bother at all. Have a good one. Bye-bye now.

Speaker 1: All right, buddy. Bye-bye.
